Now I have a complete picture. The architecture is actually correct — the LangGraph checkpointer handles all state persistence. The issue is purely about what the system prompt tells the model to do when it's in the middle of collecting details for a tool call.

Right now the model can:

Ask a question → go to END (good)
Next turn user answers → model starts fresh, may forget it was mid-booking
The model needs explicit instructions to:

Track what it's collecting — remember the intent (e.g., "booking") across question turns
Proceed to the tool immediately once all required info is in context — no extra confirmation
Never re-ask for anything already answered in the conversation
The fix is entirely in the system prompt and the _build_context function — add a pending_intent state field to track what the agent was in the middle of doing.


